body:
No. It's as simple as:

``` php
Yii::$app->response->format = \yii\web\Response::FORMAT_JSON;
return $model->attributes;
```

Keyword `render` means there is some processing of some entity composing output.
Usage `render` for the view file processing is suitable, but for simple JSON compoision  it is confusing.

I do not think such shortcut method should be added, as there could be many response formatters - not only  JSON or XML, creating method for one of them seems to be inconsistent.

If you with to add it anyway better naming can be `returnData()` or `responseData()` in following signature:

``` php
public function responseData($data, $format) {}
```

Then it can be used for `raw`, `json` or `xml`:

```
public function actionFoo()
{
    return $this->responseData($data, Response::FORMAT_JSON);
    //return $this->responseData(file_get_contents('/path/to/file.txt'), Response::FORMAT_RAW);
}
```
